</head>
<p>
<hi rend="bold">
Chibemba
</hi>
or
<hi rend="bold">
Bemba
</hi>
is
a
Bantu
language
spoken
in
<ref target="Zambia">
Zambia
</ref>
,
the
<ref target="Democratic%20Republic%20of%20the%20Congo">
Democratic
Republic
of
the
Congo
</ref>
,
and
southern
<ref target="Tanzania">
Tanzania
</ref>
.
It
is
the
biggest
ethnic
grouping
in
Zambia
,
accounting
for
over
50
%
of
the
Zambian
population
.
</p>
<p>
Bemba
people
(
<hi rend="italic">
Ababemba
</hi>
)
trace
their
origin
from
&quot;
KOLA
&quot;
in
Angola
.
The
writing
system
is
very
phonetic
and
Spanish
speakers
would
find
it
very
easy
to
learn
.
Many
Bemba
words
can
also
be
found
in
<ref target="Swahili">
Swahili
</ref>
.
</p>
